name: CMR Service-030
question:
Is the patient immunocompromised?


Immunocompromised people include those who have:

  1. Been receiving active cancer treatment for tumors or cancers of the blood
  2. Received an organ transplant and are taking medicine to suppress the immune system
  3. Received a stem cell transplant within the last 2 years or are taking medicine to suppress the immune system
  4. Received CAR-T-cell therapy, hematocrit therapy (HCT)
  5. Moderate or severe primary immunodeficiency (such as DiGeorge syndrome, Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome)
  6. Advanced or untreated HIV infection
  7. Active treatment with high-dose corticosteroids or other drugs that may suppress your immune response
